+**Created**: 2026-02-24
+
+---
+
+## Executive Briefing
+
+**Purpose**: Wire the attention system end-to-end ‚Äî deriving agent attention state per workspace and bubbling it through the UI layers (workspace card ‚Üí fleet status bar ‚Üí browser tab title). Also deliver the workspace settings page with emoji/color pickers and pop-out buttons.
+
+**What We're Building**:
+- Server-side attention derivation functions that query agent status per workspace
+- Wiring real agent data into WorkspaceCard and FleetStatusBar components (props already exist but unused)
+- Activating useAttentionTitle hook in workspace layout pages
+- A `/settings/workspaces` page with emoji picker, color picker, star toggle, remove action
+- Pop-out `[‚Üó]` buttons on agent list items and file viewer header
+- Final responsive polish pass across all pages
+
+**Goals**:
+- ‚úÖ Agent errors/questions are visible at a glance on the landing page
+- ‚úÖ Fleet status bar shows running count + attention count with navigation
+- ‚úÖ Browser tab title reflects attention state with ‚ùó prefix
+- ‚úÖ Users can customize workspace emoji and color from settings
+- ‚úÖ Key items have pop-out buttons for opening in new tabs
+
+**Non-Goals**:
+- ‚ùå SSE live-update of agent status on landing page (OOS ‚Äî polling or manual refresh is fine for now)
+- ‚ùå Full workspace CRUD (add/remove from settings ‚Äî add is already on landing page)
