+## Context Brief
+
+### Key findings from plan
+
+- **Finding: AgentInstanceStatus is 3-state** (`working` | `stopped` | `error`). "Needs attention" maps to `status === 'error'`. No "asks question" status exists in the type ‚Äî questions come via SSE events, not agent status. For Phase 5, attention = error status only.
+- **Finding: Components already accept props** ‚Äî WorkspaceCard takes `agentSummary`, FleetStatusBar takes counts, useAttentionTitle takes `needsAttention`. The UI rendering is done ‚Äî Phase 5 just wires the data.
+- **Finding: Agent API exists** ‚Äî `GET /api/agents?workspace=<slug>` returns agents filtered by workspace. Server-side DI: `IAgentManagerService.getAgents({ workspace })`.
+- **Finding: Palette constants exist** ‚Äî `WORKSPACE_EMOJI_PALETTE` (30 emojis), `WORKSPACE_COLOR_PALETTE` (10 colors with light/dark hex). Validation in service layer via `WORKSPACE_EMOJI_SET` / `WORKSPACE_COLOR_NAMES`.
+- **Finding: updateWorkspacePreferences server action exists** ‚Äî already wired for partial preference updates. Used by `toggleWorkspaceStar` form action.
+
+### Domain dependencies
+
+- `_platform/notifications`: `toast()` ‚Äî feedback on settings mutations
+- `_platform/workspace-url`: `workspaceHref()` ‚Äî URL construction for pop-out buttons and firstAttentionHref
+- `_platform/file-ops`: None directly (attention is about agents, not files)
+- Agent system (not formalized as domain): `IAgentManagerService.getAgents()`, `AgentInstanceStatus` type
+
+### Domain constraints
+
+- All new UI components go in `features/041-file-browser/`
+- Settings page route goes in `app/(dashboard)/settings/workspaces/`
+- Attention derivation is pure business logic ‚Äî no side effects, easily testable
+- Import palette constants from `packages/workflow/src/constants/workspace-palettes.ts`
+
+### Reusable from prior phases
